{#
  Kill switch confirmation modal — Plan 02-05 Task 2 / UI-SPEC §2b.

  HTMX-loaded fragment served from GET /kill/confirm-modal. Mounts into
  #modal-mount in base.html.j2 via hx-target="#modal-mount" hx-swap="innerHTML".

  CSP invariant (PATTERNS §4 anti-pattern row 7): NO inline <script> and
  NO onclick= attributes. All interactivity flows through HTMX hx-*
  attributes interpreted by the vendored htmx.min.js.

  Server-side defense (RESEARCH §3 + UI-SPEC §2b "Recommended Phase 2
  implementation"): the form POSTs to /kill, the route validates that
  `confirm.strip().upper() == "KILL"` and raises HTTPException(400) on
  mismatch. Client-side disable is polish only.
#}
<div class="modal-backdrop" id="kill-modal" role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="kill-modal-headline">
  <div class="modal">
    <div class="modal-headline" id="kill-modal-headline">Halt all trading</div>
    <div class="modal-body">
      This cancels all open orders across all strategies and halts every
      paper and live strategy. The kill state persists across process
      restarts. To resume, you must explicitly UNKILL.
      <br><br>
      <strong>Type KILL below to confirm.</strong>
    </div>
    <form hx-post="/kill"
          hx-target="#kill-banner-mount"
          hx-swap="outerHTML"
          hx-disabled-elt="find button[type='submit']">
      <label for="kill-confirm-input">Confirmation</label>
      <input type="text"
             id="kill-confirm-input"
             name="confirm"
             required
             pattern="^KILL$"
             autocomplete="off"
             autofocus>
      <div class="modal-actions mt-4">
        <a hx-get="/modal/close"
           hx-target="#modal-mount"
           hx-swap="innerHTML"
           aria-label="Cancel and close modal">Cancel</a>
        <button type="submit" class="btn-kill" hx-disable-elt="this">
          Confirm — halt all trading
        </button>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
